## 7. `DefaultCdcClient`

```java
public class DefaultCdcClient implements CdcClient {

    private final CdcConnectionProvider connectionProvider;
    private final CdcQueryProvider queryProvider;
    private final CdcResultMapper resultMapper;

    @Override
    public List<CdcEvent> poll(PollRequest request) {
        Connection connection = null;
        try {
            connection = connectionProvider.getConnection();
            String query = queryProvider.getQuery();
            return executeQuery(connection, query, request);
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            throw new CdcPollingException("Poll failed", e);
        } finally {
            connectionProvider.releaseConnection(connection);
        }
    }

    private List<CdcEvent> executeQuery(Connection connection,
                                         String query,
                                         PollRequest request) throws SQLException {
        NamedParameterQuery namedQuery = NamedParameterQuery.parse(query);
        try (PreparedStatement stmt = connection.prepareStatement(namedQuery.getSql())) {
            namedQuery.bind("fromScn", request.getFromScn(), stmt);
            namedQuery.bind("toScn", request.getToScn(), stmt);
            namedQuery.bind("maxResults", request.getMaxResults(), stmt);
            try (ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery()) {
                return resultMapper.map(rs);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

`NamedParameterQuery.parse(sql)` replaces `:paramName` occurrences with `?` and tracks their positional index for binding.

