## 10. Transaction Responsibility

**`CdcEngine` has no `@Transactional` annotation and no transaction management.** Transaction boundaries are the host service's responsibility.

In a Spring Boot host, the typical approach is to annotate the `@Scheduled` method or wrap `tick()` inside a `@Transactional` service method so that `CdcEventHandler.handle()` (inbox write) and `CheckpointStrategy.saveScn()` (checkpoint write) execute atomically in the same transaction.

The starter does not enforce this — it is a host-level architectural decision.

